# UX Flow Blueprint — Record

This document defines the complete user experience for a reality-first, human-centered platform. Every screen, action, and interaction is designed to preserve truth, originality, and calm.

---

## 1. Bottom Navigation Bar (Persistent)

- **Home / Explore** → Browse relevant boards  
- **My Boards** → Access user-created boards  
- **Record** → Create new Entry  

No notifications, no likes, no follower counts.

---

## 2. Home / Explore Boards Screen

**Layout:**  
- Pinterest-style grid of board thumbnails  
- Soft neutral background, calm spacing  
- Each board shows:
  - Title
  - Optional description
  - Number of pinned entries (optional, small, non-prominent)  

**Interactions:**  
- Tap board → enter Board View  
- Pull-to-refresh is disabled  
- Infinite scroll is disabled → use "Load more moments" button  

**Algorithmic Notes:**  
- Boards surfaced based on **user’s saved boards**, **adjacent boards**, and **temporal relevance**  
- No trending, no virality, no recent-first bias  

---

## 3. Board View Screen

**Layout:**  
- Grid of pinned Entry thumbnails  
- Each thumbnail = a still frame from the video  
- Minimal text overlay (Entry title or timestamp)  

**Interactions:**  
- Tap Entry → Entry View  
- Option to save Entry to your own boards  
- No likes, comments optional but hidden by default  

**Rules:**  
- Entries appear ordered by **discoverability score** (continuity + specificity + board migration + saves)  
- No visual indicators of popularity beyond personal relevance  

---

## 4. Entry View Screen

**Layout:**  
- Full-screen video playback  
- Soft neutral interface  
- Minimal controls:  
  - **Save** (primary action)  
  - Back to board  

**Constraints:**  
- Autoplay off  
- No filters, no AI enhancement  
- Only trimming allowed  
- Environmental audio preserved  

**Algorithmic Influence:**  
- Continuous playback does not affect ranking  
- Save counts feed into **resonance score**  

---

## 5. My Boards Screen

**Layout:**  
- List/grid of boards you own  
- Shows number of entries pinned  
- Option to create new board  

**Interactions:**  
- Tap board → Board View  
- Tap create board → Board creation form  

**Board Creation Form:**  
- Title (required)  
- Description (optional)  
- Public / Private toggle  
- Example prompt: “What moments belong here?”  

---

## 6. Record Entry Screen

**Layout:**  
- Single record button (center)  
- Minimal UI to reduce distraction  

**Constraints:**  
- Must record live (no uploads initially)  
- Duration flexible, no editing except trimming  
- Environmental audio mandatory  
- Single-take encouraged  

**After Recording:**  
- Option to pin Entry to one or more boards  
- Save Entry to your own board  
- Entry automatically timestamped (`capturedAt`)  

---

## 7. Save Flow (Primary Interaction)

**Action:** Save another user’s Entry to your board  

**Rules:**  
- Only Save is encouraged; no likes, hearts, comments, or reactions as primary signals  
- Saves contribute to **resonance score**  
- No notifications are triggered  

**Psychological Effect:**  
- Reinforces quiet participation  
- Truth and reality travel without performance pressure  

---

## 8. Onboarding Flow (First 5 Minutes)

1. Welcome Screen  
   - Message: “Record your moments. Nothing more.”  
2. Prompt: “What are you documenting right now?” → stores in `bioCurrentFocus`  
3. Board Creation Suggestion  
   - Example boards: Quiet mornings, Daily work, Starting over  
4. Record First Entry  
   - Single button, minimal UI  
5. Explore Boards  
   - See calm grid of relevant boards  

**Constraints:**  
- No follower suggestions  
- No trending entries  
- No “new” panic  

---

## 9. Key Design Principles

- Calm, neutral colors  
- Soft grid spacing, Pinterest-style  
- Minimal text  
- Slow, deliberate discovery → no infinite scroll  
- Temporal depth prioritized  
- Truth and originality protected at every interaction  

---

## 10. Future Screens (Optional, Post-MVP)

- Comment or Reflect → hidden by default, only for context  
- Profile → archive view of boards and entries, no stats displayed  
- Settings → privacy, archive export, no notifications  

---

**End of UX Flow**
